   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2573a_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>

               <note>(Copy)</note>
               <address rend="pencil">
                  <addrLine>Suvla Bay</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1915-08-24">24/8/15</date>
               </dateline>

               <salute>Dear Mr Hardy</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I am very sorry to have to tell you that <persName ref="#ps:FrankGeorge">Mr
                  George</persName> was killed on 21<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> inst. – just as
               his Company was leaving the trenches to attack. I was not with the
                        <choice><abbr>Reg<hi rend="superscript"
                     >t</hi>.</abbr><expan>Regiment</expan></choice> myself as I took over command
               of the Brigade on the 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. His Company Com­mander –
                  <persName ref="#ps:CaptainGregory">Captain Gregory</persName> – told me, as he was
               going back wounded, that <persName ref="#ps:FrankGeorge">George</persName> died
               before he could be moved into safety. <persName ref="#ps:FrankGeorge"
                  >George</persName> had done splendidly since we started fighting on the 7<hi
                  rend="superscript">th</hi> – On the 17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> he
               distinguished himself particularly &amp; brought great credit to the 5<hi
                  rend="superscript">th</hi> Dorset
                     <choice><abbr>Regt,</abbr><expan>Regiment</expan></choice>, by rushing a
               Turkish trench with his Platoon, bayonetting some 8 or 10 Turks &amp; bringing back
               14 prisoners. I sent his name forward for reward &amp; it was forwarded by the
               Brigade.</p>

            <p>I write all this to you with the request that you will let his people know – All
               papers &amp; <!-- mark up small tear --> addresses of next-of-kin were lost when my
               Adjutant was killed on the 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
               <choice><abbr>inst.</abbr><expan>??</expan></choice> otherwise I <choice><abbr>sh<hi
                        rend="superscript">d</hi></abbr><expan>should</expan></choice> not trouble
               you. The 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> Dorsets have done splendidly but at a great
               cost as our casualties have been 21 officers &amp; over 500 men, killed, wounded,
               &amp; missing.</p>


            <closer>
               <salute>Believe me</salute>
               <salute>Yours sincerely</salute>
               <signed>Cathcart Hannay</signed>
               <!-- Need to add in a double-line bracket  -->
               <signed>Brig-General</signed>
               <signed>34<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> inf Brigade</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2573a_2.jpg"/>

         </div>
      </body>
